            <li><strong>OIII and UHC Filters:</strong> Narrowband filters block light pollution while passing specific emission lines from nebulae, dramatically improving contrast for emission nebulae.</li>
            <li><strong>Expect Gray, Not Color:</strong> Most nebulae appear gray or greenish to the eye—human color vision is too insensitive in low light to detect the reds and blues prominent in photographs.</li>
